{
  "stem": "25912.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "My father had gone quite far east when Poland surrendered, and he decided to come back home.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My brother was taken prisoner by the Germans with his colleagues in Scouts, but, with the help of a Polish peasant, escaped from the POW camp.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, well, while he was-- a peasant gave him clothes, and he walked out of the camp.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they both came to Warsaw, to my mother's great dismay.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Because, at that stage, one already knew that there were various rules and regulations as far as the Jews were concerned.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I think probably about that, soon after, the Jewish star was introduced.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my brother hated it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So half the time, he wouldn't wear anything with a Jewish star.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And every time he passed a German in the street, he gave him a look as if he could kill him.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So things were rather difficult.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Also, my father's name, as a counselor of the city of Warsaw, and involved in other organizations-- Jewish ex-Combatants and so on-- his name was on various lists.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the Germans had been asking where he was.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So Mother was very, very worried.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then, in November, we got notification from the Romanian embassy that they were holding visas for Romania for my father and my brother.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "What had happened was that my uncle, who was a journalist, left with the Polish government in September of '39 and went to Romania.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And realizing what would be happening, arranged for visas for them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He didn't think at that time that my mother and myself would be at risk, so he just got the two visas.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Well, my father was not keen on leaving us behind.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
